      "id": "cf039207-f5a2-4399-842f-c59a363e492c",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The cell below establishes an automated data quality checkpoint.\n\nIt attempts to standardize the data types for the 'Recall Initiation Date' and 'Center Classification Date' columns. If it encounters records with missing values or unparseable text, it segregates them into a quarantine DataFrame and outputs an audit log to the console.\n\nThe pipeline explicitly throws a runtime error to halt further notebook execution if any anomalies are detected.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "85055168-a282-4592-b36f-31af30a94d9d",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "# Quarantine Filters creation\n## Identify text typos (rows that had data originally but became an NaT blank because they weren't real dates)\nrecall_df_typos = df['Recall Initiation Date'].isna() & recall_df_raw.notna()\ncenter_df_typos = df['Center Classification Date'].isna() & center_df_raw.notna()\n \n## Identify empty cells (broken down strictly by individual column to isolate errors cleanly)\nrecall_blank = recall_df_raw.isna()\ncenter_blank = center_df_raw.isna()\noriginally_empty_cells = recall_blank | center_blank\n \n## Combine them into a single checklist of all data errors\nall_data_errors = recall_df_typos | center_df_typos | originally_empty_cells\ndf_quarantine = df[all_data_errors]\n \n# Generate the Data Quality Audit Report\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"DATA QUALITY AUDIT REPORT\")\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\nprint(f\"Total Raw Records Loaded: {len(df)}\")\nprint(f\"Total Anomalous Records Isolated: {len(df_quarantine)}\")\nprint(f\"  - Missing 'Recall Initiation Date': {recall_blank.sum()}\")\nprint(f\"  - Missing 'Center Classification Date': {center_blank.sum()}\")\nprint(f\"  - Unparseable 'Recall Initiation Date' Strings: {recall_df_typos.sum()}\")\nprint(f\"  - Unparseable 'Center Classification Date' Strings: {center_df_typos.sum()}\\n\")\n \nif len(df_quarantine) > 0:\n    print(\"--- SAMPLE OF CORRUPTED / BLANK VALUES ---\")\n    # Pull both original raw df and output to see exactly where formatting failed\n    inspect_df = pd.DataFrame({\n        'Raw Recall Init': recall_df_raw[all_data_errors],\n        'Parsed Recall': df['Recall Initiation Date'][all_data_errors],\n        'Raw Center Class': center_df_raw[all_data_errors],\n        'Parsed Center': df['Center Classification Date'][all_data_errors]\n    })\n    # Removed .drop_duplicates() to preserve true volume and error distribution profiles\n    print(inspect_df.head(10).to_string(index=False))\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n \n    # Strict Operational Gate: Halt execution to force manual corrections\n    raise ValueError(\"Pipeline Halted: Resolve isolated errors before proceeding to visualization.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"Data Integrity Verified. Proceeding to downstream pipelines.\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)",
